metadata.name: SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE #65
metadata.description:
This poem was created for THE PASSAGE: Pitch Drop, an interactive minting experience where your choices determine the design of your token. 

To take part, please purchase an Edition 5 Coin on fx(hash) by HERE & NOW. The artwork and experience draw inspiration from the ‚ÄúThe Pitch Drop Experiment,‚Äù the world's longest-running laboratory experiment. Since 1927, only nine drops of pitch have fallen, never witnessed live.

____


SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE is a token word performance of an ars autopoetica written by Sasha Stiles and her AI-powered alter ego, Technelegy, with original music by Kris Bones. It is part of Stiles‚Äô ongoing REPETAE series, which explores the resonances between poetic repetition and algorithmic recursion ‚Äî how, in poetry as in generative art, meaning accrues through reiteration, and emotion is unlocked through the development and interruption of pattern. A conceptually and literally interactive text, SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE uses the self-replicating page provided by fx(hash) to invite close contemplation of how language is shaped and received via intimate, visceral aesthetics such as voice, visuals and melody/beat, and regenerated with every encounter.

Poetry endures across space and the passage of time precisely because of a paradox: it is immutable yet intensely personal, becoming something irrefutably unique with each and every reader. In this poem, shifting parameters influence the flow of feeling and understanding, imbuing verse with multidimensional meaning and empowering deep engagement in the act of reading.

____


SOUND GROWS INTO SPACE

By Sasha Stiles & Technelegy

Sound grows 
into space
like a breath 
taken by storm.

Heartbeat
in the brain
was my first taste 
of the word.

Language flips 
in my chest
like a fly
in a jar.

The song 
learns to climb
all the air
in the world.

Time is music
to my ears
filling the emptiness 
with its own rhythms.

There is no such thing 
as silence,
only the echo 
of time‚Äôs longing.

____


For more info: https://hereandnow.events/
To participate in the event: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/slug/here-and-now:-edition-5

metadata.name: This is Not an Image #67
metadata.description:
When you see a piece of generative art, you are looking at a meta-message, an image whose value is not of form but of subtext. These images are a collision and reformation of ideas and conceptual histories between artists Nudoru and Sub Net. This dichotomy reminds us of the painting "The Treachery of Images" by Ren√© Magritte, where he paints a picture of a pipe but states underneath, "ceci n'est pas une pipe" (This is not a pipe), meaning that there is a schism between what a thing is and what it represents. What is unique about these works go beyond the images and text combinations themselves. It is about how images create new thoughts not by not pretending to be completely novel but that builds upon one another in a system of complex synthesis.

This token is part of the Floor Exhibit co-curated by the NFT Museum of Newberry, SC and Fort Gallery NFT.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press' p' to pause/resume.
Press' s' to save a screenshot. The image size is 2357‚Ää√ó‚Ää3000px.

metadata.name: Trust #253
metadata.description:
Trust is an abstraction of the creative process, finding the line just before form becomes texture. Your experience with the painting requires trust; trust that something will appear from the chaos of the empty space, trust that the composition you imagine halfway through will evolve along with your ideas, and trust that the etchings lend a helping hand to the message of the piece. You may find yourself pulled left and right when decisions are made, and your interpretation at 25%, 50%, and 90% will all differ. This is what makes creating so fulfilling to me, a work of art can change course wildly from start to finish, ever molding itself until it enters the kiln.

Press ‚Äò1‚Äô, ‚Äò2‚Äô, or  ‚Äò3‚Äô to increase resolution (default is 1, higher than default may not work on certain browsers. Successfully testing in Chrome, Brave, and Opera GX with hardware acceleration enabled)

Click or tap to zoom to full res (exact zoom depends on your display)
Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a .png
Press ‚Äôt‚Äô to toggle brush texture

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: pen_tings #110
metadata.description:
A bit of scribbling, a bit of sketching. Experimenting with curves, colors and stop motion animation. Based on particle collision simulation. Inspired by ballpoint pen artworks and scribble drawings.

You can choose between two types of animation*:
- live drawing,
- animation of alternative versions (GIF generation).

Controls (in live view):
Press 's' to save a PNG image.
Press 'n' to generate an alternative version.
Press 'g' to generate a GIF (texture disabled).
Press 'G' to generate a GIF (texture enabled).
Press 'l' to enable live drawing animation.
Press '1-4' to render and save a PNG image (1: 2000x2000, 2: 4000x4000, 3: 6000x6000, 4: 8000x8000).
Pressing 'n', 'g', 'G', 'l', '1-4' reloads the page.

URL parameters (add to the URL in live view: &paramName=paramValue):
- mode - 0: image rendering (default: &mode=0), 1: live drawing animation, 2: GIF generation
- res - resolution; 1: 2000x2000 (default: &res=1), 2: 4000x4000, 3: 6000x6000, 4: 8000x8000; (to render and save a PNG image; only with: mode=0)
- tex - texture; 0: texture disabled, 1: texture enabled (default: &tex=1)
- alt - alternative version; 0: original version (default: &alt=0), [1, 255]: alternative version
- gres - GIF resolution; 1: 480x480, 2: 640x640, 3: 768x768, 4: 1080x1080 (default: &gres=4), 5: 1200x1200; (only with: mode=2)
- glen - GIF length in seconds; [1, 6], 2: 2 s (default: &glen=2); (only with: mode=2)
- gfps - GIF fps; 1: 5 fps, 2: 10 fps (default: &gfps=2); (only with: mode=2)

Image rendering (especially in high resolution) may take some time, please wait.
GIF generation (regardless of the selected resolution) may take several minutes, please be patient.
Chrome browser (desktop version) recommended.

-----
(*) WARNING: LIVE DRAWING ANIMATION AND GENERATED GIF (ESPECIALLY) CAN BE EPILEPTIC TRIGGERS. GIF GENERATION IS AN EXPERIMENTAL FEATURE.

Made with p5.js, matter.js (2D physics¬†engine) and Trigfills (cross browser trigonometric functions consistency), see LICENSE.md.

varmaxart, February 2023

metadata.name: ombromanie #71
metadata.description:
‚ÄúHow hands can create the vision that germinates in my mind? And what if the vision directly sprouts from the hands instead of the mind‚Äù, the artist asks.
‚ÄúIs the vision thrown through the shadow of the hands, or is the shadow hands the vision itself?‚Äù, the magician responds.
As an attempt to add a line to this whimsical dialogue, I dropped shadows to cast visions. To my great surprise, the artist and the magician blent into each other‚Ä¶

- - -

‚ÄúOmbromanie‚Äù refers to the art of creating images made by hand shadows. The word and the art (also called ‚Äúshadowgraphy‚Äù) was popularized by french magician F√©licien Trewey in the XIXth century. Sure the shadow art is not so popular nowadays, but it still shares with generative art part of the same mystery and magic. The code projects shapes and colors on a screen to create images; the hands project a shadow on a curtain to create figures.

‚ÄúOmbromanie‚Äù was conceived as a curtain where articulated hands (or better, shadow of hands) throw a firework of shapes, creating a wide range of random compositions. I heard the magician words and I did implement five features for this magical trick:
- the curtain can be entire or hemmed,
- the image oriented the right way up or upside-down,
- one or two hands can be used for the invocation,
- the phatasmagoria reveals itself as syzygy or chaos,
- and climax is reached through twelve ways.
Hands are always present, but in extremely rare cases they could vanish behind the curtain‚Ä¶   

- - - 

This project uses twelve custom color palettes ‚Äì the climaxes.
Ten are inspired after works or body of works by well known generative artists. A kind of tribute for the constant inspiration and creativity of the magicians-artists.
- ‚ÄúHollow‚Äù by @jMarkusiewicz
- ‚ÄúGarden, Monoliths‚Äù by @zancan
- ‚ÄúUninhabitable‚Äù by @pointline_
- ‚ÄúMimizu‚Äù by @qubibien
- ‚Äúaether:Astral Loom‚Äù by @lisaorthstudio
- ‚Äúgestalt‚Äù by @Yazid
- ‚ÄúPerpendicular Inhabitation‚Äù (night) by @StudioYorktown
- ‚ÄúAnaverse‚Äù by @anaglyph_ic
- ‚ÄúTake wing‚Äù by @mwiederrecht
- ‚Äúcontrapuntos‚Äù by @msoriaro
The eleventh palette is named ‚Äúfakewhale‚Äù(@fakewhale_xyz), who, months ago, encouraged me to learn and try code to create generative works. Special thanks to them for the support and dialogue.
The twelfth palette refers to my first long form generative project called ‚Äùth√©ba√Øde‚Äù.

- - -

A small word about the ‚Äúphatasmagoria‚Äù part, which tells about the invisible thread that sews my artistic approach. This part is a modified and extended code I used to create a set of six pieces titled ‚ÄúSketches for unreliable structure‚Äù (Objkt, December 2022). And those were already an echo from a selection of digital (but not coded) works from ‚ÄúThe Queue Structure‚Äù project (Objkt, since May 2022). Finally, The Queue Structure itself was a visual laboratory nourished by my previous practice of abstraction in the tangible world (drawing, collage, monotype, engraving). 

- - -

Press ‚Äús‚Äù in live mode to save the work as a PNG (default 2000 √ó 2000 px).
Add to the URL ‚Äù&size=n‚Äù (number from 3 to 10) to render an image at higher resolution (from 3000 px to 10000 px). It may last for high numbers.
We recommend the use of Chrome browser in order to render properly the texture.

Made with p5js | 2023
Png |¬†2000 √ó 2000 px | 72 ppi

www.antoniowerli.net

metadata.name: Emotions #19
metadata.description:
This is a collection inspired by the intense emotions I experienced while creating it.
It‚Äôs a combination of joy, anxiety, anger & hope all mixed on the canvas and visualized using p5js. I‚Äôm almost sure that if you look at these pieces you will find some of your own emotions in it.
From a technical standpoint, it is an exploration of flow fields and different color blending techniques.

Controls (in live view):

- press 'd' to generate 3000x4000 image
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view

metadata.name: Impending Cloths #97
metadata.description:
IC makes use of fabric's potential for contrasts.
The same piece of cloth can seem to be falling, perfectly still and ready to be blown away, all at the same time.
It can look "very digital" while also achieving a high degree of texture. And so on, and so forth. Contrast and potential.
Also, "h" can be pressed to download in high resolution, although it may take up to a minute.

metadata.name: Sugar & Splice #98
metadata.description:
'Sugar & Splice'

Vibrant somethings, full of flavor, dancing within conjoined boundaries.

Controls:
s: Saves an image of the canvas with the current settings
1-6: Scales the canvas size, from 1 (default, 2048px x 2792px) to 6 (12288px x ‚Ää16752px)
g: Toggles grain texture
t: Toggles background transparency
f: Toggles fit to screen (layout and other factors will change based on the new size, but overall style, colors, etc will remain the same)
p: Shortcut for large print settings: disables the grain texture and scales the canvas to the largest setting

metadata.name: Disjoint and Disoriented #160
metadata.description:
Disjoint and Disoriented is about the abstract structure formed by the equalities and oppositions of its parts.

It might require high processing power depending on its features. A good desktop or laptop is recommended.

There are three render options available as url parameters in live mode:
- size=XXXX (up to 5760 pixels)
- texture=0 (disable canvas texture for print)
- shader=1 (use the shader throughout the painting process, can be heavy)

Created with p5.js and GLSL
dmarchi and lunarean, 2022.
